=> @Param in Spring Data JPA is used to Bind method parameters to named parameters inside JPQL or native SQL queries. It improves:
- readability
- parameter mapping
- maintainability

Example without @Param
@Query("SELECT e FROM Employee e WHERE e.name = ?1")
Employee findByName(String name); -> Uses positional parameter (?1).

Example with @Param (recommended)
@Query("SELECT e FROM Employee e WHERE e.name = :name")
Employee findByName(@Param("name") String name);

Ques: Difference between JPQL and HQL ?
Ans: HQL = specific to Hibernate. And it has more features as compared to JPQL. For instance, database funciton, map funciton
E.g. select new map(e.name as name, e.salary as salary) from Employee e

