Ques: What is lazy evaluation in terms of intermediate and terminal function in stream ?
Ans: Intermediate operations are not executed immediately. They are only executed when a terminal operation is called.

E.g. Example: lazy evaluation in action
Stream<Employee> stream = employees.stream()
        .filter(e -> {
            System.out.println("filter " + e.getName());
            return e.getSalary() > 1000;
        });
Nothing prints yet.

stream.forEach(System.out::println);
Now filter runs.

==> Short-circuit example
 employees.stream()
        .filter(e -> e.getSalary() > 1000)
        .findFirst();
 - stop as soon as the first element is found. Do not process over entire list.
